# Avoid em dash in text

# Product and Platform Rulebook

## Design System Direction
- Prefer cohesive section-based layouts over repetitive card-heavy blocks.
- Use depth through spacing rhythm, gradients, and layered backgrounds instead of dense borders.
- Add subtle, purposeful motion (hover lift, fade/slide transitions, animated emphasis) without harming readability.
- Keep mobile-first hierarchy: clear headings, short paragraphs, obvious CTAs, and touch-friendly controls.
- Preserve Sunrise brand tone (warm, celebratory, premium-friendly) across home, features, and pricing.

## Pricing and Financial Modeling Standards
- Treat token economics as channel-weighted; do not assume one flat per-channel token cost.
- Enforce a minimum 55% gross margin target on usage-based messaging economics.
- Recompute token burn/multipliers when provider costs change (Twilio, email delivery, Stripe fee impact).
- Forecast in RM and provide:
  - 12-month base case
  - conservative and upside scenarios
  - monthly run-rate snapshot
- Always separate fixed costs (infra/domains/tools) from variable COGS (message delivery and payment leakage).

## Subscription and Token Product Rules
- Keep one wallet and one token ledger per customer account.
- Apply channel multipliers behind the scenes; keep customer UX simple and transparent.
- Subscription plans must include:
  - clear monthly included tokens
  - explicit top-up rates
  - no ambiguous "unlimited" claims without fair-use policy
- Pricing updates must include customer-facing explanation and migration notes.

## Feature Prioritization
- Focus core value loops first:
  - Event creation flow
  - Audience/contact selection
  - Template quality and consistency
  - Reliable send pipeline and delivery visibility
- De-prioritize non-core features when reliability or margin controls need attention.
- Any new feature should state expected effect on conversion, retention, reliability, or margin.

## Sunrise + Sunset Platform Architecture Direction
- Sunrise and Sunset operate as one product system under Sunrise Sunset Services.
- Keep domains separate for brand/tone positioning only; backend and account model remain shared.
- Plan domain separation at hosting/routing layer, not by splitting core data and business logic.
- Ensure pricing, balances, subscriptions, and usage policies stay consistent across both domains.
- Any domain-specific UX differences must not fragment billing, auth, or token accounting.

## Operational Governance
- Track weekly:
  - Gross revenue, net revenue (after Stripe), variable COGS, contribution margin
  - Channel mix and effective revenue/message by channel
  - Token burn/message distribution by tier
- Alert thresholds:
  - Any channel margin under 45% for 2 consecutive weeks
  - Blended margin under 55% for one full billing cycle
- Decision cadence:
  - Monthly operational review
  - Quarterly repricing review using updated vendor invoices
